#- ---Final---§0
§0
§0Fight #1, Round 1-§0
§0Tutterise vs.§0
§0Goatsedotcx§0
§0
§0The two powerhouses§0
§0of this tournament§0
§0quickly rush at each§0
§0other, with Goatse§0
§0gaining a quick lead,§0

#- but Tutter is quick to§0
§0retaliate, matching blow§0
§0for blow and managing§0
§0to stay in the center,§0
§0but Goatse's early§0
§0advantage treats him§0
§0well and he finally§0
§0takes down Tutter with§0
§0a mighty smash.§0

#- Fight #1, Round 2-§0
§0Tutterise vs.§0
§0Goatsedotcx§0
§0
§0Goatse jumps early,§0
§0catching Tuetter right§0
§0in the middle. The two§0
§0stay close to the§0
§0edge, Goatse managing§0
§0to back Tutter up no§0
§0matter where he goes.§0

#- However, Tutter's§0
§0quick maneuvering§0
§0allows him to evade§0
§0most of the blows until§0
§0he finally reaches in§0
§0behind Goatse and§0
§0cinches a KO.§0
§0
§0Fight #1, Round 3-§0
§0Tutterise vs.§0
§0Goatsedotcx§0
§0
§0Goatse charges in§0

#- quicker, catching§0
§0Tutter in his corner.§0

#- Tutter squeezes out,§0
§0but stays near the§0
§0edge, swinging wildly.§0
§0This is his undoing as§0
§0he tries a jumping§0
§0strike and gets caught§0
§0by Goatse and is flung§0
§0from the ring!§0
§0
§0

#- Fight #1, Round 4-§0
§0Tutterise vs.§0
§0Goatsedotcx§0
§0
§0Tutter dashes quickly,§0
§0but over shoots as§0
§0Goatse leaps. He§0
§0recovers quickly and§0
§0returns to the center,§0
§0catching Goatse from§0
§0behind. His fists are§0
§0relentless and he§0
§0forces a KO!§0

#- Fight #1, Round 5-§0
§0Tutterise vs.§0
§0Goatsedotcx§0
§0
§0This fight is for the§0
§0championship! Both§0
§0Tutter and Goatse§0
§0have shown grit and§0
§0power in their fights,§0
§0and neither is like to§0
§0back down easily.§0

#- The two quickly meet in§0
§0the middle and stay§0
§0there, hitting each§0
§0other blow for blow.§0
§0Finally, Tutter§0
§0retreats to the edge,§0
§0bringing Goatse with§0
§0him and sealing his own§0
§0defeat! Trapped up§0
§0against the ropes,§0

#- Goatse connects hit§0
§0after hit, destroying§0
§0Tutter's final chance§0
§0at victory, knocking him§0
§0out cold! Goatse wins!§0
§0Goatse is the winner§0
§0of the First Civcraft§0
§0Fist Fighting§0
§0Conference§0
§0Tournement!§0

#- §nFollow-Up§0
§0
§0This new fighting style§0
§0has caused quite the§0
§0uproar in CivCraftia,§0
§0and there is like to be§0
§0many more tourneys.§0
§0
§0However, I was forced§0
§0to leave Mt. Augusta in§0
§0a rush due to several§0
§0revolutionaries§0

#- initiating violence§0
§0against the state. I§0
§0was advised to flee§0
§0and I did so. Hopefully§0
§0this event will not§0
§0tarnish the future of§0
§0the Fist Fighting§0
§0League.§0

